1
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:17,520
Hey.

2
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:18,760
Wake up.

3
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:20,210
Are you okay?

4
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:22,320
She's actually sick.

5
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:25,539
Then hurry up and call the police.

6
00:01:32,479 --> 00:01:33,479
Listen, student,

7
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:35,360
even if you pretend to faint,

8
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,759
you still owe me every penny.

9
00:01:37,759 --> 00:01:39,120
I wasn't pretending to faint.

10
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,000
I am actually sick.

11
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:40,920
I know.

12
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,640
Would a normal person do what you did?

13
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,640
Let me tell you, you have two choices.

14
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:47,320
Either you pay me 3,000 yuan,

15
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,160
or you're not leaving today.

16
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:50,600
How dare you!

17
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:53,240
You actually dare to rob someone in a police station.

18
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:55,039
Officer, he's the one who extorted me,

19
00:01:55,039 --> 00:01:55,759
and hit me.

20
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:57,740
He can testify.

21
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:00,880
Don't talk nonsense, little girl.

22
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:02,600
Officer, don't listen to her nonsense.

23
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:03,960
Didn't you ask me for 3,000?

24
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:04,480
I...

25
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:05,160
Did you?

26
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,120
I did.

27
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,199
See, Officer?

28
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:08,800
He admitted it.

29
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,880
Stop making a fuss.

30
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:11,400
It doesn't matter who you ask.

31
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,000
You released them first.

32
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,840
If I hadn't stepped in to help,

33
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:16,720
do you know they would have died?

34
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:18,040
And do you know how many parents

35
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:20,240
would be heartbroken because of this?

36
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:21,079
They...

37
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,600
They are dogs.

38
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,760
Yes, they're dogs.

39
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:27,640
Why didn't you say they were dogs earlier?

40
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:29,400
Well, you didn't ask.

41
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:31,640
Wait a minute.

42
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:33,160
Are dogs not living beings?

43
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,690
Dogs are living beings too.

44
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:38,200
Young lady, you've got a sharp tongue.

45
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:39,320
Officer.

46
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,000
Please, you must help me.

47
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,600
He not only robbed but also extorted.

48
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:46,040
I'm just a girl.

49
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:48,920
What if I'm too scared to go out?

50
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:51,240
What if I'm traumatized?

51
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:54,079
So, you must help me get justice.

52
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:57,079
Everyone, the investigation is clear.

53
00:02:58,040 --> 00:03:00,520
His dog was bought legally.

54
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:01,880
It's worth 2,000.

55
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:03,920
You damaged his car, which is 1,000.

56
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,880
You let his dog go

57
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,810
and threw away his car keys.

58
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,600
This is intentional damage to property.

59
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:11,320
But...

60
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,960
Considering your intentions were good,

61
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,160
we won't hold you legally responsible.

62
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,440
However, you still have to pay compensation.

63
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:20,200
You owe him 3,000.

64
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,240
Fair and just.

65
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:22,720
And you.

66
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,280
Call the police when you have a dispute,

67
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,960
instead of getting physical with a young girl.

68
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,720
Right.

69
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,160
Got it?

70
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,520
Got it.

71
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:30,760
As for him,

72
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,960
he saved this girl in the alley.

73
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,760
It's considered a brave act.

74
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,240
Thank you.

75
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:49,320
Save it. Just give me the money.

76
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:50,680
Fine.

77
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:52,480
Here.

78
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:03,490
I'm doomed. I don't have enough money.

79
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:04,720
I'm dead meat.

80
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:09,800
Um, I don't have enough money.

81
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,600
What?

82
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:13,440
I don't have enough money.

83
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:14,800
Can I pay you later?

84
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:17,160
Why were you acting so cocky if you have no money?

85
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,480
With that attitude of yours just now,

86
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,079
I thought you were some rich kid.

87
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:21,600
Turns out you're just a nobody.

88
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,120
No, I'll definitely pay you later.

89
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:23,720
For sure.

90
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:26,960
You have to pay me back today.

91
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,000
I transferred 3,000 to you.

92
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,120
I'll get the car keys later.

93
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,320
I'll settle the score with her later.

94
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:33,480
Let her go for today.

95
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,180
You snatch her student ID,

96
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,530
and then you pay for her.

97
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,680
What's the point?

98
00:04:43,159 --> 00:04:43,880
Got it.

99
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:46,340
Wish you success soon.

100
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:51,560
Well, I...

101
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:55,080
I'm sorry.

102
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,280
I'm really sorry.

103
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:58,840
Well,

104
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,240
please wait a moment.

105
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:07,480
Thank you for earlier.

106
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,080
You still have to pay back the money.

107
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,860
What's your phone number?

108
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,340
Otherwise, how can I pay you back?

109
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:24,130
Little girl,

110
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,320
your bag.

111
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,200
I'm sorry.

112
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:30,560
I will pay back the money.

113
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,600
Thank you.

114
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,640
Where are the keys?

115
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,200
Where did they go?

116
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,980
How am I supposed to find such a small key?

117
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:02,840
Ouch.

118
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,440
How dare you.

119
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:09,770
You actually dare to rob a police station.

120
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,530
I will return the money.

121
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,210
It doesn't seem like it.

122
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,160
Tianyu.

123
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:27,560
What are you doing? You look so preoccupied.

124
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,040
Dad.

125
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,000
Nothing.

126
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,560
You came back so late.

127
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,330
Did you go out to work again?

128
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,340
I went out to help someone.

129
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,480
Actually,

130
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:47,560
I'm used to being alone all these years.

131
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:49,720
You should go back with a peace of mind

132
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,080
and continue your training.

133
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,610
Being a racer is your dream.

134
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,080
You can't just give it up.

135
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:58,880
Actually, racing and repairing cars

136
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,120
are the same to me.

137
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,170
The most important thing is

138
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:05,040
that we are all still together, aren't we?

139
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:15,960
The car brought in this morning,

140
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,000
how is it?

141
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,040
Still the same old problems.

142
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,280
Engine malfunction.

143
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:23,970
The fresh air valve and idle speed controller

144
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,040
are all aging.

145
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,440
Then remember to get more rest.

146
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,820
Don't stay up too late.

147
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,120
I'll get going then.

148
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:35,640
Okay.

149
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,320
Mom,

150
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,450
you're back.

151
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,020
How was the checkup today?

152
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,240
Not bad.

153
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,360
Mom,

154
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,740
I want to discuss something with you.

155
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,370
What a coincidence.

156
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,660
I have something to discuss with you too.

157
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,340
Next month, the school

158
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:07,840
will hold a parent-teacher meeting

159
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:09,040
for the experimental class.

160
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,500
They require us to attend.

161
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,330
I want to take you with me, okay?

162
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:16,620
A high school parent-teacher meeting? Why should I go?

163
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:17,680
If you go,

164
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:20,080
it will earn me brownie points,

165
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:20,920
you know?

166
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,400
Mom, how about this?

167
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:26,240
You transfer 3,000 yuan to me,

168
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:28,240
and I'll agree. How does that sound?

169
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,770
It's already summer vacation.

170
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,340
You stay at home every day.

171
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,220
What do you need so much money for?

172
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,120
Do you still want to

173
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,559
save face in front of the whole school?

174
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:43,200
Tell me, WeChat or Alipay?

175
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:44,380
Either is fine.

176
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,160
Mr. Zhu, given our friendship,

177
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,530
I'll be honest with you.

178
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:56,480
Your daughter didn't even take the final exam.

179
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:57,740
I had to give her a zero.

180
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:00,480
Su Wan,

181
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:02,480
why didn't you take the exam?

182
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,360
It was an accident. I...

183
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:06,240
For over ten years, I've been both father and mother,

184
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,720
taking good care of you.

185
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:09,720
What reason do you have for skipping the exam?

186
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,360
Also,

187
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,640
what exactly did you use that 3,000 for?

188
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,240
If you don't want to give it to me, fine.

189
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,960
I'll handle it myself.

190
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,120
You're always so fierce.

191
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,600
How can I get close to you?

192
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:21,920
Whenever something happens,

193
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,680
don't use your weird illness as an excuse.

194
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:26,340
I think you just have too much time on your hands.

195
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,360
Insisting on being special.

196
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:30,240
You always thought

197
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:32,560
I was faking my illness, didn't you?

198
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,200
Just to be special.

199
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,460
Aren't you?

200
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,570
Over the past few years,

201
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:40,840
at school,

202
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:43,400
I've trained tens of thousands of students,

203
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,400
many of whom have had it much harder than you.

204
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:48,280
Many of them have even been admitted to prestigious universities.

205
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:51,140
You are more dramatic and spoiled than anyone else.

206
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,960
Fear of intimacy?

207
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:55,440
Actually, it's a psychological disorder.

208
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,120
It may cause patients

209
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:59,120
when in close contact with others

210
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:02,080
to experience dizziness, nausea,

211
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,440
and palpitations.

212
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:04,680
In severe cases,

213
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,380
they might even faint.

214
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,940
So I would suggest that you

215
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:10,120
seek treatment as soon as possible.

216
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,980
You got into Lucheng University,

217
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:13,840
but you

218
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:15,360
just had to be different

219
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,160
and study whatever it's called,

220
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,560
animal science!

221
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,300
You're just being impulsive.

222
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,660
Wait, where are you going?

223
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:28,720
Just worry about your thousands of students.

224
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:30,560
Leave me alone.

225
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,520
If you dare walk out that door,

226
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:33,920
don't you ever come back!

227
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:35,780
Fine, don't come back.

228
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:57,920
Hello.

229
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,560
Hello, it's me.

230
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:00,840
Su Wan.
